  "text": "The ADS implementation in Envoy lives entirely under source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/. There are two parallel implementations: (1) a legacy one (Config::GrpcMuxImpl in grpc_mux_impl.cc/.h and Config::NewGrpcMuxImpl in new_grpc_mux_impl.cc/.h) and (2) a unified/newer one (Config::XdsMux::GrpcMuxImpl template in xds_mux/grpc_mux_impl.cc/.h, instantiated as GrpcMuxDelta and GrpcMuxSotw). The gRPC stream handling is in grpc_stream.h (GrpcStream template) with failover support in grpc_mux_failover.h. Resource subscription tracking is handled by WatchMap (watch_map.cc/.h). The delta-xDS state machine is in delta_subscription_state.cc/.h (legacy) and xds_mux/delta_subscription_state.cc/.h (unified), with the SotW counterpart in xds_mux/sotw_subscription_state.cc/.h. ACK/NACK processing uses PausableAckQueue (pausable_ack_queue.cc/.h) and update_ack.h for the ack data structure. The subscription factory (grpc_subscription_factory.cc) decides which mux implementation to instantiate based on runtime features.",
